brown.tracingplane.baggageprotocol

Class BagKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • brown.tracingplane.baggageprotocol.BagKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<BagKey>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BagKey.Indexed, BagKey.Keyed

    public abstract class BagKey
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<BagKey>

    A BagKey is used to look up data items and child bags within a baggage instance.

    BagKey instances should be created with the static methods indexed and keyed. As per the Baggage protocol, fields can either be keyed (using arbitrary bytes) or indexed (with an unsigned integer). Indexes for fields are statically assigned for efficiency in more established protocols. It is recommended to use named keys for ad-hoc data.
